[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'This is the most powerful Claude Code update in months and nobody\'s talking about it. Ultra Code allows Claude Code to handle extremely large complex task by spinning up an army of agents and I\'m not just talking about a handful. I\'m talking about potentially hundreds of'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'agents to split up the work and get it all done in one go. But the real power of Ultra Code isn\'t the amount of agents it can spawn. It\'s the fact that it builds a custom harness tuned to your specific task on the fly. Normally'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Claude Code takes a one-size-fits-all approach to solve your problems. But with this brand new feature, that\'s no longer the case. So in this video, I\'m going to break down exactly how it works so you can start leveraging this new'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'feature right away. So why should you care about Ultra Code and dynamic workflows? Well, it\'s pretty simple. It is the best way to handle large complex tasks with Claude Code. That\'s it. And the way it does it is through custom'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'harnesses. That\'s a fancy way of saying it\'s going to create a novel way to solve whatever it is you\'re trying to solve. A great example is how it handles something like deep research. If you'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have a rather complicated question like, should we migrate our checkout service to a new provider? If I\'m just using Claude Code as it normally operates, I just hop inside the prompt window and I give it this prompt, well, it\'s going to'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'use its static default harness. It\'s going to be in one single session, right? We\'re going to use one context window. It\'s going to do a handful of web searches. It\'s going to fetch the top results. It\'s going to verify, summarize, and give us a generic'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'research report. By default, when we\'re talking about static harness, what we\'re really saying is you just open up Claude Code, you\'re in one single context window, and we\'re not telling it to use sub agents or do any sort of like antagonistic review of its original'

[01:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'thought process. So, it\'s rather simple. It uses less tokens and in the end you get a generic answer. Caveat, that\'s fine for most issues. We\'re talking here today about large complex stuff. By contrast, if we use'

[01:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Ultra Code in a dynamic workflow, and I\'ll talk about in a second the difference between those two, we get a custom harness that is built for that problem. We are going to have a different way of solving that issue.'

[02:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'We\'re not just going to sit in one context window, we\'re going to bring in different agents, and the different agents are going to do different things, again, depending on the task. So, in this example, where I say, "Hey, should we migrate our checkout service to a new provider?" instead of just doing some'

[02:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'web searches and coming up with a summary, instead with a dynamic workflow, it\'s going to be like, "Okay, well, what is our checkout service?" So, it\'s going to read our billing code. It\'s actually going to go deep into how we actually operate. From there, it\'s then going to check the'

[02:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'features against the new provider\'s documentation. It\'s going to price our transaction volume. It\'s going to have an actual devil\'s advocate agent to say, "Hmm, does that actually make sense?" And then in the end, we get a specific'

[02:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'recommendation instead of a generic one. So, the big thing with dynamic workflows is again, the process by which we come up with an answer is different, it\'s customized, and it depends on the'

