AUDIO: 'context window, the worse it becomes. And the three things they talk about here can kind of all fall under the context rot umbrella. The idea of agentic laziness. You know, we\'ve all run into this where you tell Claude code'

[06:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to do something that\'s rather large in scope and it kind of does some of it. We also have self-preferential bias, referring to Claude\'s tendency to prefer its own results or findings, especially when asked to verify or judge them against a rubric. Hey, if you'

